sequenceDiagram
    participant Client
    participant Endpoint
    participant Mediator
    participant Validator
    participant Handler
    participant Domain as TierRouting
    participant DB as Database
    participant Cache as Redis
    participant Events
    participant KB as KnowledgeBase

    Client->>Endpoint: PUT /api/v1/admin/tier-routing
    Note right of Client: {tier, productionModels, defaultModel}

    Endpoint->>Endpoint: Extract payload
    Endpoint->>Endpoint: Create UpdateTierRoutingCommand

    Endpoint->>Mediator: Send(command)

    Mediator->>Validator: Validate(command)
    Validator->>Validator: Check tier is valid enum
    Validator->>Validator: Verify models exist in AiModel table
    Validator->>DB: Verify all model IDs valid
    DB-->>Validator: Models exist ✓
    Validator->>Validator: Verify defaultModel in productionModels
    Validator->>Mediator: Validation passed ✓

    Mediator->>Handler: Handle(command)

    Handler->>DB: Get or create TierRouting for tier
    DB-->>Handler: TierRouting

    Handler->>Domain: routing.Update(productionModels, defaultModel, fallback)
    Domain->>Domain: ProductionModels = models
    Domain->>Domain: DefaultModel = defaultModel
    Domain->>Domain: FallbackModel = fallbackModel
    Domain->>Domain: UpdatedAt = UtcNow
    Domain->>Events: Raise TierRoutingUpdatedEvent

    Handler->>DB: SaveAsync(routing)
    DB-->>Handler: Routing saved ✓

    Handler->>Cache: InvalidateKey("tier-routing:Premium")
    Cache-->>Handler: Cache invalidated ✓

    Handler->>Events: Publish TierRoutingUpdatedEvent
    Events->>KB: Notify model selection changed

    Handler-->>Mediator: TierRoutingDto
    Mediator-->>Endpoint: TierRoutingDto

    Endpoint-->>Client: 200 OK
    Note left of Client: {tier, defaultModel, fallbackModel}

    Note over KB: KnowledgeBase updates model selection
    KB->>KB: Refresh tier-model mapping cache
